          "rationale": "Students will learn about Christians from this time period whose faith led many of them to martyrdom.  Beginning with Peter at Pentecost, the author tells about saints such as Ignatius, Cyprian and Athanasius who defended the truths of Christianity against heresy. Instead of just giving us facts about the different people, the author tells a story about a time in their life that helps the reader understand who they are and why their story is recorded in history. This volume is a great way for students to see how these important church fathers fit into the stream of history. These were the life and times they were living— when the persecution from the Roman Empire was prevalent.",
